---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';

const title = 'Privacy Policy — MCTL Rewards';
const description =
  'How MCTL Rewards handles your data within the Telegram Mini App loyalty program.';
---

<Base title={title} description={description} path="/privacy">
  <main class="container doc">
    <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
    <span class="draft">Draft — placeholder copy, not yet legal advice</span>

    <p>
      This page describes, in plain language, how the MCTL Rewards Telegram
      Mini App ("the Service") handles your information. This is a draft and
      will be replaced with a finalized policy before general availability.
    </p>

    <h2>What we collect</h2>
    <p>
      When you open the Service from Telegram, we receive your Telegram user
      identifier and basic profile fields (such as your first name and
      username) so we can create and identify your loyalty wallet. We store
      your points balance and a history of transactions (accruals and
      redemptions) tied to that identifier.
    </p>

    <h2>How we use it</h2>
    <p>
      We use this data solely to operate the loyalty program: crediting points
      when a merchant scans your QR, letting you redeem rewards, and showing
      your transaction history. We do not sell your data.
    </p>

    <h2>Who can see your data</h2>
    <p>
      Merchant staff can see that a scan credited points to your wallet and the
      reward you redeem from them. They do not receive your full Telegram
      profile beyond what is needed to complete a transaction.
    </p>

    <h2>Retention</h2>
    <p>
      We keep your wallet and transaction records for as long as your account
      is active. You can request deletion of your account and associated data
      by contacting the community administrators.
    </p>

    <h2>Contact</h2>
    <p>
      Questions about this policy can be directed to the community
      administrators that operate this instance of the Service.
    </p>

    <a class="back" href="/">← Back to home</a>
  </main>
</Base>
